HEADWORD: Pontvolant
<hw>Pont`vo*lant"</hw> <pr>(?; F. ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pont</ets> bridge + <ets>volant</ets> flying.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A kind of light bridge, used in sieges, for
surprising a post or outwork which has but a narrow moat; a flying
bridge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ponty</ent>⟦br⟧
